title: GOP Staffer Agrees to Testify in D.C. Superior Court
text:
GOP Staffer Agrees to Testify in D.C.... GOP Staffer Agrees to Testify in D.C. Superior Court Next Story Prev Story 9 hrs ago Read more: Roll Call 
The Republican staff director of the House Oversight and Government Reform Committee has agreed to trek from the halls of Congress to a local courtroom on Nov. 19. Sean McLaughlin will testify in D.C. Superior Court on why he Chairman Jason Chaffetz, R-Utah, and ranking member Elijah E. Cummings, D-Md., do not plan to take the stand. Both moved to quash subpoenas for testimony and documents. Start the conversation, or Read more at Roll Call.
